{"data":{"wordpressPost":{"title":"Shopify Theme from Scratch Part 11: Customer Accounts &#8211; the Setup","content":"<html><head></head><body><p>\t\t\t\t<div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:23.25%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/710de8102780580262616b65a3602a5b/19bd1/part11_banner.png 163w,\n/static/710de8102780580262616b65a3602a5b/d3bcb/part11_banner.png 325w,\n/static/710de8102780580262616b65a3602a5b/dbb61/part11_banner.png 650w,\n/static/710de8102780580262616b65a3602a5b/8ff1e/part11_banner.png 800w\" src=\"/static/710de8102780580262616b65a3602a5b/dbb61/part11_banner.png\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/710de8102780580262616b65a3602a5b/19bd1/part11_banner.png 163w,\n/static/710de8102780580262616b65a3602a5b/d3bcb/part11_banner.png 325w,\n/static/710de8102780580262616b65a3602a5b/dbb61/part11_banner.png 650w,\n/static/710de8102780580262616b65a3602a5b/8ff1e/part11_banner.png 800w\" src=\"/static/710de8102780580262616b65a3602a5b/dbb61/part11_banner.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></p>\n<p>The last set of templates we need to work on are the customer accounts templates. The customer accounts templates consist of seven .liquid files that allow returning customers to create an account, view their previous orders, set their default addresses, and more.</p>\n<p>Shopify provides default customer account templates, but we&#x2019;re going to rebuild each template from scratch so that they look consistent with the rest of our themes (you&#x2019;ll see later in this Part that the default customer account templates look nothing like our current theme).</p>\n<p>But, before we move on to these new templates, we need to take some preliminary steps. Let&#x2019;s gitter done!</p>\n<p><!--more--></p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">1. Enable customer accounts in Settings</h2>\n<p>The first thing we need to do is enable the Customer Accounts feature in our shop. To do this, log in to your shop&#x2019;s admin and navigate to <em>Settings &gt; Checkout</em> and scroll down to the &#x201C;Customer Accounts&#x201D; section.</p>\n<p>Select the &#x201C;Accounts are optional&#x201D; option and click the &#x201C;Save changes&#x201D; button. Your shop now has the Customer Accounts feature enabled.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/enable-customer-accounts.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:37.691614066726785%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/e2e24cc0e4ffc842b29f161375f8ee73/aca85/enable-customer-accounts.jpg 163w,\n/static/e2e24cc0e4ffc842b29f161375f8ee73/0954f/enable-customer-accounts.jpg 325w,\n/static/e2e24cc0e4ffc842b29f161375f8ee73/a111b/enable-customer-accounts.jpg 650w,\n/static/e2e24cc0e4ffc842b29f161375f8ee73/ce471/enable-customer-accounts.jpg 975w,\n/static/e2e24cc0e4ffc842b29f161375f8ee73/c2aaa/enable-customer-accounts.jpg 1109w\" src=\"/static/e2e24cc0e4ffc842b29f161375f8ee73/a111b/enable-customer-accounts.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/e2e24cc0e4ffc842b29f161375f8ee73/aca85/enable-customer-accounts.jpg 163w,\n/static/e2e24cc0e4ffc842b29f161375f8ee73/0954f/enable-customer-accounts.jpg 325w,\n/static/e2e24cc0e4ffc842b29f161375f8ee73/a111b/enable-customer-accounts.jpg 650w,\n/static/e2e24cc0e4ffc842b29f161375f8ee73/ce471/enable-customer-accounts.jpg 975w,\n/static/e2e24cc0e4ffc842b29f161375f8ee73/c2aaa/enable-customer-accounts.jpg 1109w\" src=\"/static/e2e24cc0e4ffc842b29f161375f8ee73/a111b/enable-customer-accounts.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 11.1: Enabling customer accounts in the admin</div>\n<h2 class=\"step\">2. Create a customer account</h2>\n<p>The next thing we need to do is create a mock customer account so that we can preview and test out the customer account templates in the next Parts.</p>\n<p>Using the URL bar in your browser, navigate to <em>your-store-name.myshopify.com/account/register</em>. You will see the following:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/default_register_form.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:47.66260162601626%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/fbc3a147998fc22571dedd9ff4589c23/aca85/default_register_form.jpg 163w,\n/static/fbc3a147998fc22571dedd9ff4589c23/0954f/default_register_form.jpg 325w,\n/static/fbc3a147998fc22571dedd9ff4589c23/a111b/default_register_form.jpg 650w,\n/static/fbc3a147998fc22571dedd9ff4589c23/ce471/default_register_form.jpg 975w,\n/static/fbc3a147998fc22571dedd9ff4589c23/63be5/default_register_form.jpg 984w\" src=\"/static/fbc3a147998fc22571dedd9ff4589c23/a111b/default_register_form.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/fbc3a147998fc22571dedd9ff4589c23/aca85/default_register_form.jpg 163w,\n/static/fbc3a147998fc22571dedd9ff4589c23/0954f/default_register_form.jpg 325w,\n/static/fbc3a147998fc22571dedd9ff4589c23/a111b/default_register_form.jpg 650w,\n/static/fbc3a147998fc22571dedd9ff4589c23/ce471/default_register_form.jpg 975w,\n/static/fbc3a147998fc22571dedd9ff4589c23/63be5/default_register_form.jpg 984w\" src=\"/static/fbc3a147998fc22571dedd9ff4589c23/a111b/default_register_form.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 11.2: the default Shopify register.liquid template</div>\n<p>As I mentioned earlier in the intro, Shopify actually provides all of the customer templates for you, but they&#x2019;re no good if they don&#x2019;t look like the rest of your theme, right? In the next Parts we&#x2019;re going to rebuilt these templates to make them look like the rest of our theme. For now though, we&#x2019;re going to use Shopify&#x2019;s default template to create a mock account.</p>\n<p>Go ahead and use the register form in Figure 11.2 to create a customer account. Once complete, you should see your new customer account in the &#x201C;Customers&#x201D; section of your admin (Figure 11.3).</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/test-account.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:50.59171597633136%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/977228acf029c5eff8515f23b92f927b/aca85/test-account.jpg 163w,\n/static/977228acf029c5eff8515f23b92f927b/0954f/test-account.jpg 325w,\n/static/977228acf029c5eff8515f23b92f927b/a111b/test-account.jpg 650w,\n/static/977228acf029c5eff8515f23b92f927b/ce471/test-account.jpg 975w,\n/static/977228acf029c5eff8515f23b92f927b/07d81/test-account.jpg 1014w\" src=\"/static/977228acf029c5eff8515f23b92f927b/a111b/test-account.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/977228acf029c5eff8515f23b92f927b/aca85/test-account.jpg 163w,\n/static/977228acf029c5eff8515f23b92f927b/0954f/test-account.jpg 325w,\n/static/977228acf029c5eff8515f23b92f927b/a111b/test-account.jpg 650w,\n/static/977228acf029c5eff8515f23b92f927b/ce471/test-account.jpg 975w,\n/static/977228acf029c5eff8515f23b92f927b/07d81/test-account.jpg 1014w\" src=\"/static/977228acf029c5eff8515f23b92f927b/a111b/test-account.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 11.3: The customer account you created will appear in the Customers page of the admin</div>\n<h2 class=\"step\">3. Add all the Customer Account templates</h2>\n<p>Next we&#x2019;re going to add the customer account templates to our Template Editor so that we can edit them. Navigate to your Template Editor, and click the &#x201C;Add a new template&#x201D; button in the sidebar. Add all <strong>seven</strong> of the available customer account templates (Figure 11.4).</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/customer-account-templates-list.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:67.0196671709531%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/ea1d2ae2542e8cf7e61a0f2fdc116c67/aca85/customer-account-templates-list.jpg 163w,\n/static/ea1d2ae2542e8cf7e61a0f2fdc116c67/0954f/customer-account-templates-list.jpg 325w,\n/static/ea1d2ae2542e8cf7e61a0f2fdc116c67/a111b/customer-account-templates-list.jpg 650w,\n/static/ea1d2ae2542e8cf7e61a0f2fdc116c67/3f0e4/customer-account-templates-list.jpg 661w\" src=\"/static/ea1d2ae2542e8cf7e61a0f2fdc116c67/a111b/customer-account-templates-list.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/ea1d2ae2542e8cf7e61a0f2fdc116c67/aca85/customer-account-templates-list.jpg 163w,\n/static/ea1d2ae2542e8cf7e61a0f2fdc116c67/0954f/customer-account-templates-list.jpg 325w,\n/static/ea1d2ae2542e8cf7e61a0f2fdc116c67/a111b/customer-account-templates-list.jpg 650w,\n/static/ea1d2ae2542e8cf7e61a0f2fdc116c67/3f0e4/customer-account-templates-list.jpg 661w\" src=\"/static/ea1d2ae2542e8cf7e61a0f2fdc116c67/a111b/customer-account-templates-list.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 11.4: Adding the seven customer account templates</div>\n<p>You should now have the following in your theme&#x2019;s Template Editor:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>customers/account.liquid</li>\n<li>customers/activate_account.liquid</li>\n<li>customers/addresses.liquid</li>\n<li>customers/login.liquid</li>\n<li>customers/order.liquid</li>\n<li>customers/register.liquid</li>\n<li>customers/reset_password.liquid</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 class=\"step\">4. Enable the &#x201C;theme&#x201D; customer layout</h2>\n<p>Finally, we&#x2019;re going to tell our theme to use our own customer account templates. This is done through a field in the Theme Settings titled &#x201C;Customer Area Layout&#x201D;.</p>\n<p>Navigate to the Theme Settings, and under <em>Additional Layouts &gt; Customer Area Layout</em>, select &#x201C;theme&#x201D; (Figure 11.5). Hit save.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/theme-setting.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:46.04550379198266%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/fcbdaa3884bcc6eb2b66aac281d7ca2d/aca85/theme-setting.jpg 163w,\n/static/fcbdaa3884bcc6eb2b66aac281d7ca2d/0954f/theme-setting.jpg 325w,\n/static/fcbdaa3884bcc6eb2b66aac281d7ca2d/a111b/theme-setting.jpg 650w,\n/static/fcbdaa3884bcc6eb2b66aac281d7ca2d/7edfd/theme-setting.jpg 923w\" src=\"/static/fcbdaa3884bcc6eb2b66aac281d7ca2d/a111b/theme-setting.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/fcbdaa3884bcc6eb2b66aac281d7ca2d/aca85/theme-setting.jpg 163w,\n/static/fcbdaa3884bcc6eb2b66aac281d7ca2d/0954f/theme-setting.jpg 325w,\n/static/fcbdaa3884bcc6eb2b66aac281d7ca2d/a111b/theme-setting.jpg 650w,\n/static/fcbdaa3884bcc6eb2b66aac281d7ca2d/7edfd/theme-setting.jpg 923w\" src=\"/static/fcbdaa3884bcc6eb2b66aac281d7ca2d/a111b/theme-setting.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 11.5: Telling the theme to load the theme&#x2019;s customer account templates</div>\n<p>Now that we&#x2019;ve selected the &#x201C;theme&#x201D; option, our theme will use the templates that we added in Step 3 from now on. You&#x2019;ll see this if you go back to the register page (<em>your-store-name.myshopify.com/account/register</em>) that we visited in Step 2. Instead of the default Shopify template that we saw earlier (Figure 11.2), the theme will now load the customers/account.liquid template we added earlier.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/07/register_after.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:55.98802395209581%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/1d3f7675ee39d55d6d44ed6de8dbd2ab/aca85/register_after.jpg 163w,\n/static/1d3f7675ee39d55d6d44ed6de8dbd2ab/0954f/register_after.jpg 325w,\n/static/1d3f7675ee39d55d6d44ed6de8dbd2ab/a111b/register_after.jpg 650w,\n/static/1d3f7675ee39d55d6d44ed6de8dbd2ab/ce471/register_after.jpg 975w,\n/static/1d3f7675ee39d55d6d44ed6de8dbd2ab/4450c/register_after.jpg 1002w\" src=\"/static/1d3f7675ee39d55d6d44ed6de8dbd2ab/a111b/register_after.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/1d3f7675ee39d55d6d44ed6de8dbd2ab/aca85/register_after.jpg 163w,\n/static/1d3f7675ee39d55d6d44ed6de8dbd2ab/0954f/register_after.jpg 325w,\n/static/1d3f7675ee39d55d6d44ed6de8dbd2ab/a111b/register_after.jpg 650w,\n/static/1d3f7675ee39d55d6d44ed6de8dbd2ab/ce471/register_after.jpg 975w,\n/static/1d3f7675ee39d55d6d44ed6de8dbd2ab/4450c/register_after.jpg 1002w\" src=\"/static/1d3f7675ee39d55d6d44ed6de8dbd2ab/a111b/register_after.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 11.6: your theme now uses the customer account templates in your Template Editor!</div>\n<p>Your customer account templates will look a little jumbled now because we haven&#x2019;t applied our own markup and CSS yet, but we&#x2019;ll take care of that in the next Parts &#x1F642;</p>\n<p>That&#x2019;s all for now!</p>\n<p><a href=\"/shopify-theme-from-scratch/\">&#x2190; Back to table of contents</a>\t\t</p>\n</body></html>","wordpress_id":3566},"allWordpressWpComments":{"edges":[{"node":{"content":"<p>Hi, I wonder where I find that {% layout settings.customer_layout %} ? Is it now gone? It is strange that the system lets me create a new account.xxx.liquid so easily but I really don&#8217;t see a way to use it&#8230; Perhaps only via an app somehow?</p>\n","author_name":"Josef Habr","date":"February 16th, 2016"}},{"node":{"content":"<p>Thank you very much for these articles. They&#8217;ve been very helpful!</p>\n<p>For anyone looking for the Customer Area Layout and cannot find it, I think it&#8217;s part of an old version of Shopify. I think the current version uses the themes templates automatically.</p>\n<p>In your customer templates there is this code at the top &#8211; {% layout settings.customer_layout %} Remove this and you will get the same result as Figure 11.6.</p>\n<p>Hope that helps anyone who runs into this in the future</p>\n","author_name":"Eloise","date":"November 5th, 2015"}},{"node":{"content":"<p>Ray, Luke, Jonny:<br />\nStep 4 of the tutorial appears to be deprecated in the current version of Shopify.  It stumped me at first too.</p>\n<p>To get Shopify to use our own templates for the customer account pages, remove the first line {% layout settings.customer_layout %} from each customer template (theme_root/templates/customers/*.liquid)</p>\n","author_name":"Mike","date":"November 2nd, 2015"}},{"node":{"content":"<p>I cant find the above either!</p>\n","author_name":"Jonny","date":"August 4th, 2015"}},{"node":{"content":"<p>What do you mean by Theme settings and how do you navigate towards it?</p>\n","author_name":"Luke","date":"July 23rd, 2015"}},{"node":{"content":"<p>Hello,</p>\n<p>First of all, this is such a great tutorial.. </p>\n<p>I have question regarding on &#8220;Customer Area Layout‚Äù, I can&#8217;t find this.. </p>\n<p>Thanks.</p>\n","author_name":"Ray","date":"July 4th, 2015"}}]}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"shopify-theme-from-scratch-part-11","wordpressId":3566,"newerPostSlug":"shopify-theme-from-scratch-part-12","olderPostSlug":"shopify-theme-from-scratch-part-10"}}